latestIgtvVideos.caption:
ANNOUNCING - The Invisible Kashmir - The Firdous Trail
Some things stay invisible. They like it that way. Saffron is one such thing. Kashmir produces the world’s best saffron in its undulating lands of Pampore. Everybody wants it but very few know it’s origins - where it comes from, how three strands of a purple flower becomes the world’s most expensive spice. 
For the first time ever, KOI is giving only 8 families the chance to explore this hidden land - at the peak of its harvest season. Don’t miss this chance. 
Oct 8-14
Kashmir 
Srinagar Pampore Gulmarg Pahalgam

latestPosts.caption:
A tiny hamlet tucked straight out of a fairy tale - just an hour from Udaipur has become India’s best place to see wild leopards - roaming free 
The drive from Udaipur is ethereal - butter smooth roads, lush green mountains and forests on both sides - quite unlike what you would expect Rajasthan to be 
The best and only place to stay here is the luxurious @jhadolsafari - right on a pristine lake dotted with hills on all sides in the heart of the hinterland 
Just 10 minutes into our safari drive, we saw a huge pack of jackals feeding on their kill and then the show stopper - a big male leopard - happy after his dinner rolling on the ground and giving us a viewing of a lifetime 
Head to Jhadol if you are a wildlife enthusiast

latestPosts.caption:
The valour of Marwar runs through the veins of its women and its Marwari horses - this land is replete with stories of strong women - from Rani Padmini of Chittor to Maharani Gayatri Devi of Jaipur. 
About a 1000 years ago, it is believed that a ship carrying exceptionally beautiful Arabian stallions sunk near the Indian west coast. The strongest and luckiest of the horses managed to swim to the coast where they were found by the Rathore rulers of Marwar in what is today’s Rajasthan. The rulers were exceptional horsemen themselves. Conquered by the stallions’ beauty, they captured the Arabians and brought them back to their kingdom where they bred them with their existing flock made of strong, resilient ponies that were descendants of horses brought by conquerors from Afghanistan and Mongolia. The Marwari, and its curly tipped ears that touch in the shape of a heart was born. 
Photographing the fabulous new regal collection by ace Rajasthani designer @manshabymaanvi at the most stunning new location at Nathdwara - @thehillhousenathdwara

latestPosts.caption:
The Smell that Never Left Her 
The letter she never wrote 

Some encounters leave that permanent mark - indelible, unquenching, incomplete 
But it immerses us in its entirety - devours us almost 
There is no certain future to it, nor does it have an entity in the present 
But it feels like ours 
Their smell - wafts through our nostrils like a continuous gush of air we breathe - a necessity almost 
We want to confide the illegitimacy of the feeling but it is best left unsaid or unfelt 
We want to immortalise it in form through a private personal letter 
But even words find no form in the burnt paper we didn’t give birth to 

We just let that feeling be 
That smell entertain us privately in the confines of our mind 
Because what cannot be - is best left unsaid, unfelt, however much it burns us in the gates of hell 

The Hill House 
NATHWARA
